Server creation = nodejs+ express

basic commands
-------------

1)Creation of the package.json - npm init

2) creation of node modules - npm i express (installing of express)

basic steps
-----------

1) Creating a folder (BankServer)
2)Create package.jsom
3)Install express
4)Create index.js
5)Import express inside the index.js
6)Create an app using the express
7)Setup port number
8)resolving http request
    get- to get the data
    post- to  post the dat
    put- update data partially
    patch- update data completely
    delete- to delete the data completely


 9)HTTP rESPONSE code
    1xx - Information
    2xx - successful
    3xx - Redirection
    4xx - Client error
    5xx - server error


10) JWT token

   Install JWT - npm i jsonwebtoken
   To generate a token - sign()

11) Middleware

It comes in the middle of the request and response nodejs excecution process

   1) Application speccific middleware - For entire middleware
      req,res,next
   2) Router specific middleware - Valiidate token - verify()  jwtwebtoken

12) Database integration
   1) Install mongoose - npm i mongoose

13) Asynchronous function resolving - promise
    
      1)Resolving State - .then()
      2)Reject state -catch()


14) CORS -Cross Origin Resource Sharing

   install cors - npm i cors


   port 4200(angular) ---------request-------> 3000(node) (receive)


15) Asynchronous call -Rxjs (Reactive Extension for JavaScript)

JS - promise
TS - RxJs (library)

  1)Observable
     a)resolved - Subscribe()
     b) reject - catch()







       


      

